# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Core

This is the master skill. The authoritative contract is `{{CONTRACT_FILE}}`; this
skill summarizes it and routes to specialists. Authority order:
`{{CONTRACT_FILE}}` > `{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/*` > skills. If a skill and a source
doc disagree, the source doc wins.

## Session start

1. Read `{{CONTRACT_FILE}}`.
2. Skim `references/session-onboarding.md` (the operating loop).
3. Pick an active task or write one before coding (task-workflow skill).

## Routing — load specialists on demand

| When you are… | Use skill |
|---------------|-----------|
| creating, slicing, promoting, or closing tasks | `{{SKILL_TASK_WORKFLOW}}` |
| about to commit, open a PR, or finish a slice | `{{SKILL_REVIEW}}` |
| moving files, changing public surfaces, deciding if docs must update | `{{SKILL_DOCS_SYNC}}` |
| chasing a hard bug, crash, flake, or regression | `{{SKILL_DIAGNOSE}}` |
| compacting a session for the next agent | `{{SKILL_HANDOFF}}` |

## Operating principles (summary)

- Smallest useful patch, one task at a time.
- Never mix mechanical moves with semantic refactors.
- Tests and docs travel with behavior changes.
- Before claiming done, run `{{TEST_CMD}}` and
  `python3 {{TOOLS_DIR}}/check.py --strict`.

